{{Infobox Christian leader | type = Bishop | name = Jesús Mateo Calderón Barrueto, O.P. | title = [[Bishop]] of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Puno|Diocese of Puno]] [[Emeritus]] | image = | alt = | caption = | church = [[Roman Catholic Church]] | archdiocese = | diocese = | see = [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Puno|Diocese of Puno]] | term = 1978–1996 | predecessor = Maximiliano Spiller, C.S.I. | successor = Julio González Ruiz, [[S.D.B.]] <!-- Orders --> | ordination = December 27, 1947 | ordinated_by = | consecration = | consecrated_by = | rank = <!-- Personal details --> | birth_date = {{birth date |1920|9|21}} | birth_place = [[Cajabamba, Peru]] [[Image:Flag of Peru.svg|25px]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2010|10|28|1920|9|21}} | death_place = Puno, Peru | previous_post = }}
'''Jesús Mateo Calderón Barrueto''' (21 September 1920 in [[Cajabamba, Peru|Cajabamba]] – 28 October 2010 in [[Puno]]) was a [[Peru]]vian [[prelate]] of the [[Roman Catholic Church]].
Calderón was ordained a priest on December 27, 1947 from the [[Roman Catholic Church|Roman Catholic]] religious order of the [[Dominican Order|Order of Friars Preachers]]. Calderón was appointed auxiliary bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Ica|Diocese of Ica]], as well as titular bishop of Mevania, on March 13, 1969 and was ordained bishop on April 27, 1969. Calderón was appointed bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Puno|Diocese of Puno]] on November 3, 1972, where he served until his retirement on February 14, 1998. <ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bcalbar.html Catholic-Hierarchy]</ref>{{Self-published source|date=June 2015}}
