'''Sangat Singh [[Saini]]''' was a general in the army of [[Ranjit Singh|Maharaja Ranjit Singh]] in the [[Sikh Empire]]. He oversaw the operations in the [[Gurdaspur District]]. His headquarters were in [[Batala]]. Sangat Singh was rewarded {{convert|300|acre|km2|adj=on}} estate from Maharaja Ranjit Singh for bravery in battle when Sangat Singh conquered a post in the [[Afghanistan|Afghan]] region and brought back the Golden Sword of the Afghan ruler to Maharaja Ranjit Singh. The estate is now known as [[Sangatpur]] in Batala, Gurdaspur District, India.<ref name ="Gurdarshan1">Gurdashan Singh Dhillon, "The Sikh Rule and Ranjit Singh", A Gateway to Sikhism</ref>

