In addition to publishing books, Tharpa also supplies audio books,<ref>[http://www.tharpa.com/us/meditation-buddhist-audio-books.html ''Buddhist audio books''] at Tharpa Publications, retrieved 2009-03-22.</ref> Buddhist art,<ref>[http://www.tharpa.com/us/buddhist-art.html ''Buddhist art''] at Tharpa Publications, retrieved 2009-03-22.</ref> and [[sadhana]]s for prayer and meditation.<ref>[http://www.tharpa.com/us/buddhist-prayer.html ''Prayer Booklets''] at Tharpa Publications, retrieved 2009-03-22.</ref>

The 'half-drop' repeat patterns used in some NKT-IKBU artwork as well as [[sadhana]] covers, such as the peony-style flower and emblem of Manjushri (a sword and book upon a lotus) were designed by Robert Beer.<ref>Beer, Robert. ''The Encyclopedia of Tibetan Symbols and Motifs''. Boston: Shambala, 1999. p. 368.</ref>

