'''Victor Tungilik''' was an [[Inuit]] religious figure who was both a Christian and a traditional ''[[angakkuq]]'' ([[medicine man|spiritual healer]]) of [[Anglican]] parents.<ref>Aparecida Vilaça, Robin Wright. ''Native Christians: Modes and Effects of Christianity Among Indigenous Peoples of the Americas''. Ashgate Publishing, Ltd., 2009 {{ISBN|0-7546-6355-8}}, {{ISBN|978-0-7546-6355-3}}</ref> Tungilik later eschewed his ''angakkuq'' practices and moved to [[Naujaat]].<ref>http://www.tradition-orale.ca/english/life-story-victor-tungilik-70.html</ref>

